      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="238">Magnesium compounds have wide applications. Magnesium hydroxide </text>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="0">– Mg(OH</text>
      <subsup>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="0">)</text>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="13" fc="0" fa="1" charset="238"></text>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="0">2</text>
      </subsup>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="0"> – is used in medicine as ”milk of magnesia”, an antacid. Magnesium sulphate(VI) – MgS</text>
      <subsup>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="0">O</text>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="13" fc="0" fa="1" charset="238"></text>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="0">4</text>
      </subsup>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="0"> – also known as Epsom salts - is used as a purgative in medicine. Alloys of magnesium with aluminium, zinc, cerium, zirconium and thorium are the lightest of engineering alloys, used in the construction of aircraft and spacecraft. </text>
   </par>
